"Guenta","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Marco, Salvatore, Salvo, Santo, Carmine, Rocco, Sal.","Probably a metathesized form of Italian   Giunta  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Giunta","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Salvatore, Santo, Angelo, Sal, Carmelo, Ciro, Edvige, Marco, Rocco, Aldo, Antonio, Carmela.","Italian: from a short form of the personal name <i>Bonag(g)iunta</i>, literally ‘good addition’, a name commonly given in the late Middle Ages to a long-awaited or much-desired son. Found throughout Italy, the name is common only in the south, specifically in Calabria and Sicily."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Guenta verch Gruffydd was born in 1050, in Wales as the daughter of Gruffydd ap Llewelyn King of Wales and Unknown. She married Flaald fitz Flaald Seneschal de Dol-de-Bretagne about 1066, in France. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1084, in her hometown, at the age of 34, and was buried in Plénée-Jugon, Côtes-d'Armor, Brittany, France."},"et":{"1050–1084":"1050–1084","1046–1084":"1046–1084","1066–Male":"1066–Surnud","1078–1126":"1078–1126","1007–1063":"1007–1063","–Female":"Surnud","1007":"1007","1126":"1126","1046":"1046","1078":"1078","1066":"1066","1063":"1063","1084":"1084","1050":"1050","5 August 1063":"5. august 1063","about 1066":"umbes 1066","Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Dol de Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, St Malo, Bretagne, France":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Wales":"Wales","Plenee-Jugon, Departement des Côtes-d'Armor, Bretagne, France":"Plénée-Jugon, Côtes-d'Armor, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1050–1084":"1050–1084","1046–1084":"1046–1084","1066–Male":"1066–Kuollut","1078–1126":"1078–1126","1007–1063":"1007–1063","–Female":"Kuollut","1007":"1007","1126":"1126","1046